    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabric made of undyed wool, noted for being extremely soft, light in weight, graceful in draping, and formerly commonly used as a material for ladies' daytime dresses. Although it was originally left in its natural color, it was later dyed in various colors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
